# *.onnx used to be blanket-ignored, but Day 14 deployment (Vercel, git-based
# build) needs models/*.onnx and rag/embedding_model/model.onnx actually
# committed -- see docs/architecture.md for why this is safe (both models
# are well under GitHub's 100MB per-file limit, no git-lfs needed).
# best_*.pt/.pth training checkpoints are still excluded -- those are large,
# dev-machine-only artifacts, never needed at runtime.
*.pt
*.pth
weights/
.ipynb_checkpoints/
agent/traces.jsonl
mlruns/
evaluation/drift_report.html
.vercel
.coverage
.coverage.*
mlflow.db
# leftover from the abandoned chromadb-based RAG index (Day 14 moved to
# rag/embeddings.json + plain numpy cosine search, see rag/retriever.py) --
# not read by any code path anymore.
rag/chroma_db/
# huggingface_hub's own download cache (lock files/metadata), not the actual
# model files -- rag/embedding_model/model.onnx and tokenizer.json themselves
# ARE committed (see the *.onnx note above), just not this cache junk.
rag/embedding_model/.cache/
